SALMONELLOSIS, (Serotype I 4,5,12,i-), SPROUTS - USA: (ILLINOIS)
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Wed 22 Dec 2010
Source: The Packer [edited]
<http://thepacker.com/Source-still-sought-in-Jimmy-John-s-salmonella-cases/Article.aspx?oid=1293642&fid=PACKER-TOP-STORIES&aid=2189>


Although health authorities have linked a salmonella outbreak to
alfalfa sprouts served at Jimmy John's Gourmet Sandwiches in
Illinois, the company's owner said not all victims reported eating
sprouts. In a 21 Dec 2010 letter to franchisees, Jimmy John Liautaud
said 28 of 40 salmonella victims interviewed by public health
officials reported eating at Jimmy John's. Of those, 25 reported
eating sprouts, he said.

The Illinois Department of Public Health confirmed 43 cases of
illness involving the same salmonella serotype. Many victims, the
department said, reported eating sprouts at Jimmy John's restaurants
in 10 Illinois counties: Adams, Champaign, Cook, DuPage, Kankakee,
Macon, McHenry, McLean, Peoria and Will.

In his letter, Liautaud said the Champaign, IL-based chain is
temporarily removing sprouts from Illinois menus while awaiting
direction from the state. "No source has been found yet, this is a
precautionary measure," according to the letter.

The company's main supplier of alfalfa sprouts tested negative for
salmonella on 17 Dec 2010, Liautaud said, and restaurants tested to
date were also negative. The state also asked Jimmy John's to test
all food-handling employees at 2 restaurants in Champaign. Those
tests were still ongoing.

[Byline: Mike Hornick]

